benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/invoicePayments/{paymentId}/customFields - Add custom fields to payment

covered: Valid Payload: TC01, TC03, TC05, TC06, TC09, TC12, TC15, TC18, TC21, TC24, TC25 cover successful creation, error handling, and integration scenarios for valid payloads.
Header Handling: TC02 and TC03 cover optional and required headers (X-Killbill-CreatedBy, X-Killbill-Reason, X-Killbill-Comment).

Error Handling: TC08 (malformed JSON), TC09 (missing header), TC10 (invalid paymentId format), TC11 (non-existent payment), TC12 (unauthorized access), TC13 (service unavailable), TC16 (missing required fields), TC14 (malicious input), TC18 (network timeout), TC20 (duplicate fields behavior), TC17 (unexpected query params), TC22 (performance), TC23 (concurrent requests under SLA).

Edge Cases: TC04 (existing fields remain), TC06 (extra/unexpected parameters depending on strictness), TC07 (empty body), TC07 also covers design-based outcomes, TC09 covers missing headers, TC11 covers non-existent payment, TC15 covers large payloads, TC16 covers partial/missing required fields, TC19 (concurrency), TC20 (duplicate fields), TC21 (unicode), TC24-25 integration persistence/consistency, TC26 accessibility.
gaps: Authorization coverage beyond 401/403 edge case exists in TC12; explicit tests for role-based access or token refresh scenarios are not present.
Caching behavior (ETag, Cache-Control) is not covered for POST responses.
Rate limiting/throttling tests are not present (only performance under load is covered in TC22/TC23 but not explicit rate limiting behavior).
Pagination is not applicable to POST, but there is no explicit validation of idempotency or duplicate submission handling beyond field duplication (TC20).
Validation breadth for CustomField properties could be enhanced with more negative tests (e.g., invalid fieldValue types, invalid objectType values) beyond those implied in TC16/TC06.
recommendations: Add explicit authorization/role-based access tests (e.g., valid token with insufficient scope vs. valid token with proper scope).
Include tests for caching headers on POST responses (ETag, Cache-Control) to confirm caching policy.
Expand rate-limiting/throttling tests to verify behavior under bursty traffic and ensure proper 429 responses where applicable.
Enhance validation tests for CustomField schema (e.g., invalid fieldValue types, invalid objectType values, and boundary value checks).
Clarify idempotency/duplicate submission handling with a dedicated test verifying behavior when identical payloads are posted multiple times (beyond TC20).
Consider a focused test for Unicode handling across all fields to complement TC21 (ensure round-tripping through persistence and retrieval).
Add targeted negative tests for edge cases in headers (e.g., invalid header formats, extremely long header values).
Maintain TC26 accessibility alignment with automated checks or an alternate accessibility test path to ensure documentation remains accessible.
